Do you even have a license?

00:30.964 --> 00:32.799
Why, I have an English one.

00:32.800 --> 00:33.933
Uh, does that count?

00:33.934 --> 00:35.103
Apparently not.

00:37.438 --> 00:40.107
Listen.
Now we have the chance.

00:40.108 --> 00:41.574
Shall we just blow out of here

00:41.575 --> 00:42.975
and go to Sag Harbor
for the weekend?

00:42.976 --> 00:44.544
You don't want to meet them.

00:44.545 --> 00:45.778
Of course I do.

00:45.779 --> 00:47.380
I'm thrilled.
I'm delighted.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.549
No, no. I mean, you know,
kids and parents.

00:49.550 --> 00:50.983
I mean,

00:50.984 --> 00:52.852
it's always a bit
tricky introducing...

00:52.853 --> 00:54.687
It's too late now.
They've seen us.

00:54.688 --> 00:56.423
Hi. Hi. Thomas,

00:56.424 --> 00:59.126
I... You... I want you
to be yourself,

00:59.127 --> 01:00.860
and I want you to have
fun and...

01:00.861 --> 01:02.262
But, you know,
sometimes these...

01:02.263 --> 01:03.663
They can be a little...
And you can...

01:03.664 --> 01:05.397
And you... you know what?
Never mind.

01:05.399 --> 01:07.135
It's fine. Let's go in.
It's fine.

01:08.836 --> 01:10.537
Welcome, welcome.

01:10.538 --> 01:11.439
Hi.

01:11.440 --> 01:13.506
Glo, bring your tuchus
over here.

01:13.507 --> 01:16.143
You heard her, Glo. Get
your tuchus over there.

01:16.144 --> 01:18.010
- Hi, honey.
- Hi.

01:18.011 --> 01:20.012
- How are you?
- Hi, Mom. Hi.

01:20.013 --> 01:21.148
Nice to see you.

01:21.149 --> 01:22.215
- Hi, darling.
- Both of you,

01:22.216 --> 01:23.616
This is Thomas Pembridge.

01:23.617 --> 01:25.785
- How do you do?
- Oh, you must
be very special.

01:25.786 --> 01:28.221
She never brings any
of her boyfriends home.

01:28.222 --> 01:31.224
Well, she has horrible
taste in men.

01:31.225 --> 01:32.625
You said it.

01:32.626 --> 01:34.161
Oh, he's fun.

01:34.162 --> 01:36.229
And this was at the prom.

01:36.230 --> 01:38.998
Oh. Never seen so much hair.

01:38.999 --> 01:40.567
And her date. My God.

01:40.568 --> 01:42.569
Looks like a porcupine
with acne.

01:42.570 --> 01:45.572
Well, actually, he now
runs a tech company

01:45.573 --> 01:47.174
worth 7 billion.

01:47.175 --> 01:49.041
Hmm. Oh, my Lord.

01:49.042 --> 01:51.244
Who's this little butterball?

01:51.245 --> 01:52.745
Well, that's Glo at age 12.

01:52.746 --> 01:55.982
We used to call her
Princess Twinkie.

01:55.983 --> 01:57.317
Oh.

01:57.318 --> 02:00.253
You don't say.
Well, hello, Princess Twinkie.

02:00.254 --> 02:02.255
All right. That's enough.

02:02.256 --> 02:04.191
I was a very heavy little girl.

02:04.192 --> 02:06.826
I promised myself I was
going to lose 40 pounds

02:06.827 --> 02:09.729
and move somewhere
with a library

02:09.729 --> 02:12.232
just as soon as
I possibly could.

02:12.233 --> 02:13.700
I think we hit a nerve.

02:13.701 --> 02:15.535
She always thought
she was too good for us.

02:15.536 --> 02:17.670
Yeah. And, you know,
I'm always trying

02:17.671 --> 02:20.207
- to get her to lighten up.
- That... That's not true.

02:20.208 --> 02:22.209
- It's not false.
- Mom,

02:22.210 --> 02:24.811
I got the strudel cake
you like in the kitchen.

02:26.880 --> 02:28.481
So listen, kid,

02:28.482 --> 02:30.751
what are your intentions
for our daughter?

02:32.753 --> 02:34.754
Oh, well, not marriage.

02:34.755 --> 02:37.023
Do you think I want
to be number 5?

02:37.024 --> 02:38.958
So that's it, honey.

02:38.959 --> 02:40.328
No grandchildren.

02:42.596 --> 02:43.630
Y...

02:43.631 --> 02:45.097
Ha!

02:45.098 --> 02:46.533
- Oh, you!
- Look at his face!

02:46.534 --> 02:48.435
He believe we were going
to give him the third degree.

02:48.436 --> 02:49.802
- You got me.
- Really?

02:49.803 --> 02:50.870
That's a good one.

02:50.871 --> 02:52.305
What's so funny?

02:52.306 --> 02:54.307
Your parents are
being abusive to me.

02:54.308 --> 02:55.408
I love them.

02:55.409 --> 02:56.876
They're fantastic.

02:56.877 --> 03:00.313
Well, I'm glad everyone's
getting along so well.

03:00.314 --> 03:01.482
Come here.

03:04.084 --> 03:05.952
Bye. Bye, Glo.

03:05.953 --> 03:07.554
- Wow.
- Bye.

03:07.555 --> 03:09.622
I think that went splendidly.

03:09.623 --> 03:11.558
Oh, I'm glad
you had so much fun.

03:11.559 --> 03:12.959
Well, you would, too,
if you removed

03:12.960 --> 03:15.127
that lumpy piece of stick
from up your ass.

03:15.128 --> 03:18.431
I will, and then I will
hit you over the head with it.

03:18.432 --> 03:20.467
Oh, ho ho.
That's the spirit.

03:20.468 --> 03:22.269
Listen, we have to go
to your place tonight.

03:22.270 --> 03:23.670
I've got a lodger.

03:23.671 --> 03:25.872
I think I'd just like
to take a night to myself.

03:25.873 --> 03:28.040
Oh, well, I mean, what
the hell did I say?

03:28.041 --> 03:30.410
Oh. You know, I...

03:30.411 --> 03:32.580
I don't know
what I was thinking.

03:34.682 --> 03:37.750
4 in the morning,
and you still can't sleep.

03:37.751 --> 03:40.287
Maybe a little music will help.

03:42.022 --> 03:43.323
John Sebastian,

03:43.324 --> 03:44.491
hey, keep on playing,

03:44.492 --> 03:45.825
but don't play for me

03:45.826 --> 03:46.926
because I'm home.

03:46.927 --> 03:48.027
I'm fine, okay?

03:48.028 --> 03:49.529
I don't... You know?

03:49.530 --> 03:53.700
A man without a house
who says he's home.

03:53.701 --> 03:56.303
A man who goes to prison
and says he's free.

03:56.304 --> 04:00.139
Is he a child,
a genius, or a madman?

04:00.140 --> 04:01.474
Shut up, John Sebastian!

04:01.475 --> 04:04.777
Whoa. Who... What...
What's all the noise for?

04:04.778 --> 04:06.313
Sorry, sorry, Maestro.
Sorry. I...

04:06.314 --> 04:07.547
What are you throwing?

04:07.548 --> 04:08.748
It's just...
It's John Sebastian...

04:08.749 --> 04:10.450
Oh, my God, you're
doing the bubbles

04:10.451 --> 04:11.851
- in the house again.
- I have to.

04:11.852 --> 04:13.620
There's something I'm
trying to figure out,

04:13.621 --> 04:14.987
but I can't until I sleep,

04:14.988 --> 04:16.956
and I can't sleep until
I can figure it out.

04:16.957 --> 04:20.959
Because I saw Melody Yang
to an amazing bubble,

04:20.961 --> 04:23.162
a big one, and then a little one

04:23.163 --> 04:24.464
that goes inside that bubble,

04:24.465 --> 04:27.166
and then another one

04:27.167 --> 04:28.401
which circled around the bubble.

04:28.402 --> 04:29.669
You know, I...

04:29.670 --> 04:31.371
I've been wanting
to tell you something.

04:31.372 --> 04:32.772
Yes, tell me, tell me.

04:32.773 --> 04:34.807
Well, it's about Gloria and me.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.644
I... I just don't know
what the hell I'm doing.

04:37.645 --> 04:39.346
At the beginning
of this thing, it was...

04:39.347 --> 04:41.348
She was so much fun, you know.

04:41.349 --> 04:43.950
We had a wonderful time
together, and it...

04:43.951 --> 04:47.053
And then, for no reason,
she just turned.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.220
It's always like that.

04:48.221 --> 04:49.456
- No fun...
- Always...

04:49.457 --> 04:50.723
- ...anymore.
- ...like that.

04:50.724 --> 04:52.725
- Nothing.
- One day it's okay,

04:52.726 --> 04:55.395
and then next day's
really weird,

04:55.396 --> 04:56.763
and nobody knows why.

04:56.764 --> 04:58.130
- Yeah.
- It's like the orchestra,

04:58.131 --> 04:59.466
you know?
They were together.

04:59.467 --> 05:01.233
- Yeah.
- Now it separated,

05:01.234 --> 05:03.903
together again, but who
knows what's gonna happen?

05:03.904 --> 05:05.372
It's always like this.
It's always changing.

05:05.373 --> 05:07.641
- Feh.
- Yeah. Hey.

05:09.042 --> 05:10.677
What about the sticky stuff?

05:10.678 --> 05:12.879
Oh, right, remember that one?

05:12.880 --> 05:14.046
Yeah, you're going...

05:14.047 --> 05:15.748
Yes. I finished it
before going to Venice.

05:15.749 --> 05:17.216
- Oh, shoot.
- Yes.

05:17.217 --> 05:18.919
But try this. Try this.

05:20.287 --> 05:21.454
Oh, my God.

05:21.455 --> 05:22.655
Give it... Give it a try.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.724
- Jesus.
- And you'll see.

05:29.296 --> 05:30.963
Right.

05:30.964 --> 05:32.400
Look at that.

05:34.768 --> 05:35.936
Wow.

05:38.672 --> 05:41.307
I fee like you're making
me play second fiddle

05:41.308 --> 05:42.676
in our relationship.

05:43.877 --> 05:46.546
Yes, I know I actually
play second fiddle.

05:46.547 --> 05:48.416
Why would you say that?

05:50.584 --> 05:52.652
How am I gonna get people
to play this for me?

05:52.653 --> 05:55.422
It's too small for
the orchestra people.

05:55.423 --> 05:57.289
Well, never
underestimate the power

05:57.290 --> 05:58.691
of free pizza and beer.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.693
I'm using it to build
a whole cabaret.

06:00.694 --> 06:02.729
It's the fire alarm.

06:02.730 --> 06:04.864
We got to go
to the courtyard.
Leave your stuff.

06:08.168 --> 06:09.670
Watch it, tuba.

06:29.457 --> 06:31.323
Hey, are you Esther Ohnn?

06:31.324 --> 06:33.292
- I am.
- Oh, wow.

06:33.293 --> 06:34.694
I'm a really big fan of yours.

06:34.695 --> 06:36.328
I know that sounds,
like, super nerdy.

06:36.329 --> 06:37.664
I just think it's really cool

06:37.665 --> 06:39.298
that you turned down
a residency at Julliard

06:39.299 --> 06:40.567
for the Moscow Symphony,

06:40.568 --> 06:42.535
and that you play
with Björk, and...

06:42.536 --> 06:44.471
Yeah.
I'm Hailey Rutledge.

06:44.472 --> 06:46.806
You're the one who threw up
on Andrew Walsh.

06:46.807 --> 06:51.143
Well, yeah, I threw up
around Andrew Walsh,

06:51.144 --> 06:52.211
and he fired me.

06:52.212 --> 06:53.746
Good. Because
after he asked me

06:53.747 --> 06:55.347
to wash his laundry by hand,

06:55.348 --> 06:57.484
I was out of there.
He is the bane.

06:57.485 --> 06:58.951
Yeah.
He's kind of the worst.

06:58.952 --> 07:01.655
Well, it is good to meet
another cult survivor.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.056
Uh, hey,

07:04.057 --> 07:06.859
I am putting together
an ensemble for an event,

07:06.860 --> 07:09.161
and I was just wondering
if you wanted to play.

07:09.162 --> 07:10.597
Does it pay?

07:10.598 --> 07:11.698
Do you like free beer?

07:11.699 --> 07:13.365
Yes. Who's conducting?

07:13.366 --> 07:14.400
I am.

07:14.401 --> 07:15.401
Okay. Cool.

07:15.402 --> 07:16.569
What?

07:16.570 --> 07:18.170
I'll do it.

07:18.171 --> 07:19.672
Shock and awe, right?

07:19.673 --> 07:22.576
Yeah. Shock and awe.

07:25.345 --> 07:27.114
All right, see you at rehearsal.

07:29.082 --> 07:31.651
It's some kind of
metacarpal fracture

07:31.652 --> 07:34.587
which explains
the chronic inflammation.

07:34.588 --> 07:36.789
What about another round
of injections?

07:36.790 --> 07:39.291
We can keep on with that
and the physio,

07:39.292 --> 07:44.531
but in the end
you're probably going
to need the surgery.

07:44.532 --> 07:47.166
However, if the surgery
goes well,

07:47.167 --> 07:50.237
there's a good chance you'll
still be able to play.

07:52.640 --> 07:54.373
I don't get it.

07:54.374 --> 07:55.542
Excuse me?

07:55.543 --> 07:56.776
The sign.

07:56.777 --> 07:59.445
Is that for the nurses
or for us?

08:02.315 --> 08:03.550
How did you do that?

08:03.551 --> 08:05.653
Too many threes.

08:06.654 --> 08:07.955
Too much Bach.

08:09.022 --> 08:11.023
Uh, threes...
Is that basketball?

08:11.024 --> 08:14.594
Yes. Kevin Masers.
New York Knicks.

08:14.595 --> 08:16.796
Cynthia Taylor,
New York Symphony.

08:16.797 --> 08:18.064
Oh, cool. You know,

08:18.065 --> 08:20.032
I play a mean "Für Elise"
on the piano.

08:20.033 --> 08:22.134
- Yeah?
- Or at least I could.

08:23.403 --> 08:24.571
You had surgery?

08:24.572 --> 08:28.274
Yeah, ten days ago.
What about you?

08:28.275 --> 08:30.677
My metacarpal is jacked.

08:30.678 --> 08:32.578
A guy on my team had that.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.046
You know what helped him?

08:34.047 --> 08:35.313
Bourbon.

08:35.315 --> 08:36.716
With me.

08:36.717 --> 08:38.751
It was probably
just the bourbon.

08:38.751 --> 08:41.587
But you probably shouldn't
have it without me,

08:41.589 --> 08:42.589
just to be safe.

08:42.590 --> 08:44.222
Ahem. Ms. Taylor.

08:44.224 --> 08:45.491
Uh, here's a prescription.

08:45.492 --> 08:47.093
Remember to stay off that arm.

08:47.094 --> 08:48.094
Understand?

08:49.262 --> 08:50.598
Yep.

08:58.371 --> 09:00.272
Pull.

09:00.273 --> 09:02.141
Eh, kind of.

09:02.142 --> 09:03.943
Glad we didn't have to break in.

09:03.944 --> 09:05.244
Oh, yes.

09:05.245 --> 09:07.013
I can't believe these
things are still here.

09:07.014 --> 09:08.815
Oh, Maestro says
the bubbles can stay.

09:08.816 --> 09:11.217
We're in the bubble with them?

09:11.218 --> 09:12.318
- Eh.
- I don't know.

09:12.319 --> 09:13.753
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.321
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

09:15.322 --> 09:17.724
Hey. Subbing for Betty?

09:17.725 --> 09:19.659
Yeah, just until the auditions,

09:19.660 --> 09:21.393
which is awesome
because I only have,

09:21.394 --> 09:22.995
like, $40 in my bank account.

09:22.996 --> 09:24.664
Do you know what piece
you're playing?

09:24.665 --> 09:26.532
Uh, yeah, I have
a couple of options.

09:26.533 --> 09:28.334
Let me know if you
want some help.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.335
Thanks.

09:30.370 --> 09:31.704
I missed this.

09:33.373 --> 09:35.107
- Hey, everyone.
- Maestro.

09:35.108 --> 09:36.242
Look at this.

09:36.243 --> 09:38.678
Wow, we... we're back
in our home.

09:38.679 --> 09:40.680
Wait. Why so few of you?

09:40.681 --> 09:41.981
It's the chamber group

09:41.982 --> 09:44.016
for the big donors'
gala, Maestro.

09:44.017 --> 09:45.017
What?

09:45.018 --> 09:46.919
Hi. Hello.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.487
Sit down, sit down, please.

09:48.488 --> 09:50.156
Take a seat. Take a seat.

09:50.157 --> 09:51.258
An, uh...

09:52.793 --> 09:54.962
How do you
guys feel? Okay?

09:55.896 --> 09:57.463
- Yeah?
- Good.

09:57.464 --> 09:58.597
Not tired?

09:58.598 --> 10:00.266
- No.
- Okay.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.601
Um...

10:03.771 --> 10:05.504
are those trees on?

10:05.505 --> 10:07.840
Is it me, or...
Or are they, like...

10:07.841 --> 10:09.475
- No, they have lights.
- They have them.

10:09.476 --> 10:10.710
- They have lights.
- Yeah.

10:13.546 --> 10:15.148
All right. Elegy.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.366
Maestro.

10:35.402 --> 10:36.568
Maestro.

10:36.569 --> 10:38.370
Hey...

10:38.371 --> 10:40.172
Okay. Ahem.

10:40.173 --> 10:41.708
Okay, let's keep on rehearsing.

10:41.709 --> 10:42.975
- You need a rest.
- Okay. No.

10:42.976 --> 10:44.576
- It's okay.
- Mm-hmm?

10:44.577 --> 10:45.545
Okay, I'm okay, I'm okay.

10:45.546 --> 10:46.779
I'm okay. Okay.

10:46.780 --> 10:48.247
Why don't you rehearse?
Okay?

10:48.248 --> 10:50.149
Why don't you keep on
rehearsing a little bit?

10:50.150 --> 10:52.351
Okay? Let's
keep on doing it,

10:52.352 --> 10:56.155
and I will be from here
supervising. Okay?

10:56.156 --> 10:58.424
- But you guys do it...
- Let's help him.

10:58.425 --> 11:00.305
...in the... in the best
way possible, you know?

11:03.430 --> 11:05.331
Ha ha.

11:05.332 --> 11:08.101
Oh, no. We're not
doing this one.

11:09.369 --> 11:12.404
It's okay. Use it
for warming up. Okay.

11:17.110 --> 11:18.445
Oh, man.

11:44.337 --> 11:45.438
Hai Lai?

11:47.040 --> 11:48.674
Cynthia?

11:48.675 --> 11:49.910
Tanya?

11:59.219 --> 12:01.154
Ai, those trees.

12:03.556 --> 12:04.858
Hello?

12:06.927 --> 12:09.162
Heh. You awake?

12:10.798 --> 12:12.099
Yeah.

12:13.066 --> 12:14.967
- Hi.
- Hi.

12:14.968 --> 12:16.468
I'm Rodrigo de Sousa.

12:16.469 --> 12:18.604
Ah, I know who you are.

12:18.605 --> 12:20.439
You're the guy
on all the posters.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.474
Yes. Yes, I am.

12:22.475 --> 12:24.476
Yes, and you...
You are the...

12:24.477 --> 12:25.812
I'm just security.

12:25.813 --> 12:28.915
Yeah? I've never
seen you before now.

12:28.916 --> 12:30.716
I've been here 25 years.

12:32.552 --> 12:34.287
Whoa.

12:36.489 --> 12:37.689
What time is it?

12:37.690 --> 12:39.092
3 a.m.

12:39.993 --> 12:41.660
- Here?
- Mm-hmm.

12:41.661 --> 12:43.662
Did you get some rest?

12:43.663 --> 12:46.999
Oh, yes. Yes, I...
I really needed...

12:47.000 --> 12:49.368
I'm going to get some maté.
Do you want some?

12:49.369 --> 12:50.369
Some what?

12:52.305 --> 12:54.406
- Were you here when...
- Yeah, I...

12:54.407 --> 12:56.175
Pembridge's "Eroica" was.

12:56.176 --> 12:58.010
I don't remember
that one so much.

12:58.011 --> 12:59.545
Yeah.
That... That's, like...

12:59.546 --> 13:01.747
I'm sorry, man. You know,
sometimes I just...

13:01.748 --> 13:03.382
I fall asleep.

13:03.383 --> 13:04.450
Why?

13:04.451 --> 13:07.486
You know, I...
I like jazz, Coltrane.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.889
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, Coltrane...

13:09.890 --> 13:11.023
Sure, no question.

13:11.024 --> 13:12.191
- And the...
- Of course.

13:12.192 --> 13:14.260
We can see the link
from Stravinsky.

13:14.261 --> 13:15.995
- Yeah.
- That's good.

13:15.996 --> 13:20.766
Yeah, but, you know, like,
Beethoven, Chopin, Bach...

13:20.767 --> 13:22.268
You... you don't
appreciate them?

13:22.269 --> 13:23.870
Yeah, yeah, yeah, they're okay,

13:23.871 --> 13:25.071
but, you know, they...

13:25.072 --> 13:26.338
I think I need that rhythm,

13:26.339 --> 13:27.739
you know, that kind of swing,

13:27.740 --> 13:29.041
like the pop

13:29.042 --> 13:31.343
that you get from,
like, jazz solos

13:31.344 --> 13:32.711
- and stuff like that.
- What...

13:32.712 --> 13:34.380
What do you think, then, that...

13:34.381 --> 13:36.582
I mean, what would
make it better for you?

13:36.583 --> 13:39.218
Uh, better costumes with it.

13:39.219 --> 13:40.619
Oh, yeah, well, definitely that.

